# Obsidian Markdown Standard (Vault-Wide)

This vault uses Obsidian-flavored Markdown (OFM), not plain CommonMark.

## Required conventions

- Use wikilinks for internal notes: `[[Path/Note]]`.
- Use embed syntax for transclusion/media: `![[Path/Note]]`, `![[image.png]]`.
- Keep Dataview blocks valid when present (do not rewrite as plain markdown tables unless asked).
- Preserve YAML frontmatter and Obsidian metadata fields when editing existing notes.
- Keep headings/task lists compatible with Obsidian core features.

## Editing behavior

- When touching existing notes, preserve current OFM constructs unless user explicitly requests conversion.
- Do not replace wikilinks with `[label](path.md)` for internal links.
- Avoid plugin-specific syntax additions unless already used in the target file or explicitly requested.
- Keep markdown human-readable in Obsidian source mode (avoid HTML unless necessary).

## New note defaults

- Prefer short frontmatter only when useful (e.g., `type`, `status`, `tags`, `created`).
- Prefer internal references via `[[...]]`.
- Use relative vault paths in links, without `.md` suffix.
